Scraping FIFA ratings for individual players

  • FIFA is a video game that lets you play a soccer game
  • It features real teams and players, and updates the statistics for each player every year based on their performance
  • These stats can be found online on websites such as futhead
  • For our example, let's pick Sergio Aguero

    def get_attributes1617(link):
    import requests
    response = requests.get('https://www.futwiz.com' + link)
    if response.status_code == 200:
        page_content = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html5lib')
        
        #grunt work - every stat is in a different div with a separate name
        #could perhaps just extract data from every nth div - but the number of divs between separation is not uniform
        #this runs pretty quickly so don't see the any downside atm
        rating = page_content.find('div', class_='ovrblock').get_text()
        position = page_content.find('b').get_text()
        acceleration = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour accelerationstat').get_text()
        sprint_speed = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour sprintspeedstat').get_text()
        pace = str((int(acceleration) + int(sprint_speed))/2)
        positioning = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour positioningstat').get_text()
        finishing = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour finishingstat').get_text()
        long_shot = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour longshotstat').get_text()
        penalties = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour penaltiesstat').get_text()
        shot_power = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour shotpowerstat').get_text()
        volleys = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour volleysstat').get_text()
        shooting = str((int(positioning)+int(finishing)+int(long_shot)+int(penalties)+int(shot_power+volleys))/6)
        crossing = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour crossingstat').get_text()
        curve = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour curvestat').get_text()
        freekick_accuracy = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour fkaccstat').get_text()
        longpass = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour longpassstat').get_text()
        shortpass = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour shortpassstat').get_text()
        vision = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour visionstat').get_text()
        passing = str((int(crossing)+int(curve)+int(freekick_accuracy)+int(longpass)+int(shortpass)+int(vision))/6)
        agility = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour agilitystat').get_text()
        balance = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour balancestat').get_text()
        ball_control = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour ballcontrolstat').get_text()
        reactions = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour reactionsstat').get_text()
        composure = str(0)
        dribbling = str((int(agility)+int(balance)+int(ball_control)+int(reactions)+int(composure))/5)
        heading_accuracy = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour headingaccstat').get_text()
        interceptions = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour tactawarestat').get_text()
        marking = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour markingstat').get_text()
        stand_tackle = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour standingtacklestat').get_text()
        slide_tackle = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour slidetacklestat').get_text()
        defending = str((int(heading_accuracy)+int(interceptions)+int(marking)+int(stand_tackle)+int(slide_tackle))/5)
        aggression = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour aggressionstat').get_text()
        jumping = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour jumpingstat').get_text()
        stamina = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour staminastat').get_text()
        strength = page_content.find('div', class_='individual-stat-bar-stat textcolour strengthstat').get_text()
        physicality = str((int(aggression)+int(jumping)+int(stamina)+int(strength))/4)
        
    return rating, position, pace, acceleration, sprint_speed, shooting, positioning, finishing, long_shot, penalties, shot_power, volleys, passing, crossing, curve, freekick_accuracy, longpass, shortpass, vision, dribbling, agility, balance, ball_control, reactions, composure, defending, heading_accuracy, interceptions, marking, stand_tackle, slide_tackle, physicality, aggression, jumping, stamina, strength

    def scrape_function(url):
    dataset = list()
    next_page_token = True

    while next_page_token != False:
      
        response = requests.get(url)
        
        if response.status_code == 200:
            page_content = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html5lib')
        
            names = page_content.find_all('p', class_='name')
            team = page_content.find_all('p', class_='team')
            name_team = zip(names, team)
    
            #get links to pages with attributes
            for (item_name, item_team) in name_team:
                
                link = item_name.find('a').get('href')
                player_name = item_name.get_text().replace('\n', '')
                team_name = item_team.get_text().split('|', 1)[0].replace('\n', '')[:-1]
                if link.find('/career-mode/player/-/') == -1:
                    attributes = get_attributes(link)
                    dataset.append((player_name, team_name, *attributes))
                    
                        
        else:
            print('Error!')
    
        next_url = page_content.find('div', class_='col-2 next').find('a')
        if next_url == None:
            next_page_token = False
        else: 
            url = "https://www.futwiz.com" + next_url.get('href')
                   
    return dataset

    Scraping League performance statistics

  • Next up, we got the performances for all the players in the Premier League (UK first division soccer league)
  • This translates to the "In Real Life" performance of the player, for 38 games during a season so one full year
  • You can find statistics related to a player's performance, such as amount of goals scored, on the official website
    • In [10]:
    from IPython.display import Image
Image("epl-player.png")
    Out[10]:

  • There are 4 four player cathegories, related to their positions on the field: Goalkeeper, Defender, Midfielder and Forward

  • Each category gets different statistics displayed - for instance the goalkeepers get information as to how many saves the y produce whereas forwards get info as to how many goals they score

  • The website is built on javascript, which means we had to use Selenium to "fake" a Chrome browser opening the website and clicking on elements manually

  • We scraped four seasons: 15/16, 16/17, 17/18 as well as the still ongoing 18/19

    #Helper function to get the statistics of a given player, depending on the position:
def get_info(epl_id,position,season): 
    # create a new Chrome session
    driver = webdriver.Chrome(chrome_driver_path)
    response = driver.get('https://www.premierleague.com/players/'+epl_id+'/player/stats?co=1&se='+season)
    time.sleep(2)
    source = driver.page_source
    driver.quit()
    stat_list = []
    page_content = BeautifulSoup(source,'lxml')
    main = page_content.find('ul', class_='normalStatList block-list-2 block-list-2-m block-list-padding')
    stats = main.find_all('span')
    
    if position=='GOALKEEPER':
        for item in stats[1:16:2]+stats[18:25:2]+stats[27:32:2]+stats[34::2]:
            try:
                x = item.find('span').get_text()
                x = x.replace(',','')
                if "%" in x:
                    x = float(x.replace('%',''))/100
                else:
                    x = float(x)
                stat_list.append(x)

            #In case the data is missing, so we don't get an error that would stop the program from running
            except AttributeError:
                stat_list.append(0)
        return(stat_list)
    
    if position=='DEFENDER':
        for item in stats[1:36:2]+stats[38:53:2]+stats[55:62:2]+stats[64::2]:
            try:
                x = item.find('span').get_text()
                x = x.replace(',','')
                if "%" in x:
                    x = float(x.replace('%',''))/100
                else:
                    x = float(x)
                stat_list.append(x)
                
            except AttributeError:
                stat_list.append(0)
        return(stat_list)
                
    if position=='MIDFIELDER':
        for item in stats[1:24:2]+stats[26:41:2]+stats[43:50:2]+stats[52::2]:
            try:
                x = item.find('span').get_text()
                x = x.replace(',','')
                if "%" in x:
                    x = float(x.replace('%',''))/100
                else:
                    x = float(x)
                stat_list.append(x)
                
            except AttributeError:
                stat_list.append(0)
        return(stat_list)
                
    if position=='FORWARD':
        for item in stats[1:24:2]+stats[26:35:2]+stats[37:44:2]+stats[46::2]:
            try:
                x = item.find('span').get_text()
                x = x.replace(',','')
                if "%" in x:
                    x = float(x.replace('%',''))/100
                else:
                    x = float(x)
                stat_list.append(x)
                
            except AttributeError:
                stat_list.append(0)
        return(stat_list)

    #position is a str, can be one of:
#GOALKEEPER, DEFENDER, MIDFIELDER, FORWARD
#season is a strn can be one of:
#'27' is 2014/2015
#'42' is 2015/2016
#'54' is 2016/2017
#'79' is 2017/2018
#'210' is 2018/2019
def scrape_epl(position,season):
    driver = webdriver.Chrome(chrome_driver_path)
    response = driver.get("https://www.premierleague.com/stats/top/players/appearances?po="+position+"&se="+season)
    #Note that I chose Appearances as the statistic because if the players did not appear, then by definition their 
    #stats are all zero
    time.sleep(10)
    source = driver.page_source
    page_content = BeautifulSoup(source,'lxml')
    name_list = []
    attributes = []
    
    #dismissing the cookies accept prompt:
    cookies_prompt = driver.find_element_by_css_selector('body > section > div > div > span')
    if (cookies_prompt != None):
        cookies_prompt.click()
        time.sleep(3)
    next_page_check = page_content.find('div',class_='paginationBtn paginationNextContainer')
    while next_page_check!=None:
        main = page_content.find('tbody', class_='statsTableContainer')
        players = main.find_all('a',class_='playerName')
        for player in players:
            name_list.append(player.get_text())
            epl_identifier = ''.join([n for n in player.get('href') if n.isdigit()])
            attributes.append(get_info(epl_identifier,position,season))
            #Then it clicks the next page button and goes to the next page
        next_button = driver.find_element_by_xpath('//*[@id="mainContent"]/div/div/div[2]/div[1]/div[3]/div[2]')
        ActionChains(driver).move_to_element(next_button).perform()
        next_button.click()
        time.sleep(10)
        source = driver.page_source
        page_content = BeautifulSoup(source,'lxml')
        next_page_check = page_content.find('div',class_='paginationBtn paginationNextContainer')
        #If this is the final page, it will go out of the loop
        #Otherwise it will go back to the top of the loop and fetch data frm the current page
            
    main = page_content.find('tbody', class_='statsTableContainer')
    players = main.find_all('a',class_='playerName')
    for player in players:
        name_list.append(player.get_text())
        epl_identifier = ''.join([n for n in player.get('href') if n.isdigit()])
        attributes.append(get_info(epl_identifier,position,season))

    driver.quit()
    
    attributes = list(zip(*attributes))
    dataset = list(zip(name_list, *attributes))
    
    return dataset

    def create_table(position,season):
    
    #get the dataset:
    dataset = scrape_epl(position,season)

    #naming the season properly:
    corresp = {'27':'2014_15','42':'2015_16','54':'2016_17','79':'2017_18','210':'2018_19'}
    years = corresp[season]
    
    #writing to a file
    file_name = years+'_'+position+"_stats.csv"
    with open(file_name, "w") as f:
        writer = csv.writer(f)
        if position == 'GOALKEEPER':
            writer.writerow(['name','saves','penalties saved','punches','high claims','catches','sweeper clearances','throw outs','goal kicks','clean sheets','goals conceded','errors leading to goal','own goals','yellow cards','red cards','fouls','goals','assists','passes','passes per match','accurate long balls'])
        if position == 'DEFENDER':
            writer.writerow(['name','clean sheets','goals conceded','tackles','tackle success','last man tackles','blocked shots','interceptions','clearances','headed clearance','clearances off line','recoveries','duels won','duels lost','successful 50/50','aerial battles won','aerial battles lost','own goals','errors leading to goal','assists','passes','passes per match','big chances created','crosses','cross accuracy','through balls','accurate long balls','yellow cards','red cards','fouls','offsides','goals','headed goals','goals with right foot','goals with left foot','hit woodwork'])
        if position == 'MIDFIELDER':
